int user = 3;
boolean status = true;
int i = 2;

while(i < user) {
    if(user % i == 0) {
        status = false;
        break;
    }
    i++;
}

if (status==true)
    System.out.println("Prime");
else
    System.out.println("Not a prime");

A number is prime if:
It has exactly 2 factors → 1 and itself
Start checking from i = 2


Why?
Dividing by 1 is always true
Dividing by itself is always true
